 ways in which queer individuals express and discipline their desire, represent themselves, build communities, and subvert heterosexual expectations. It covers a wide range of music including medieval songs, works by Handel, Tchaikovsky and Britten, women's music and disco, performers such as Judy Garland, Melissa Etheridge, Madonna, and Marilyn Manson, and the movies The Rocky Horror Picture Show and Hedwig and the Angry Inch.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aGender identity in music. 0aHomosexuality and music. 0aMusic and literature. 0aMusicxHistory and criticism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  abritten.  abroadway.  aclassical music.  acultural studies.  adesire.  adisco.  agender norms.  agender roles.  agender studies.  agender.  ahandel.  ahedwig and the angry inch.  ahomosexuality.  ajudy garland.  algbt music.  algbt.  amadonna.  amarilyn manson.  amedieval songs.  amelissa etheridge.  amusic studies.  amusic.  amusical creatures.  amusical gods.  amusical theater.  amythology.  anonfiction.  apop music.  apopular culture.  aqueer theory.  aqueer.  arocky horror.  aseduction.  asexuality.  asirens.  asubversion.  atchaikovsky.  aulysses.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052021587040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092174040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520921740423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520921740/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY